value.excerpt: The US Food and Drug Administration is on the cusp of approving the nation's first Covid-19 vaccine without a permanent leader at the helm, and a nomination doesn't appear to be in sight.

value.excerpt: The US House should be able to access some of Donald Trump's tax records through a subpoena to his accounting firm Mazars USA, a federal judge in Washington, DC, ruled on Wednesday.

value.title: Manchin has 'serious concerns' about Dems' $3.5T spending plan, signaling trouble for Biden agenda
value.excerpt: Sen. Joe Manchin on Wednesday morning said he has "serious concerns" about his party's massive $3.5 trillion spending plan, signaling that he may intend to block much of the package supported by President Biden over inflation and debt concerns.

value.title: Biden nominates Mueller deputy Elizabeth Prelogar for US solicitor general
value.excerpt: President Biden nominated Elizabeth Prelogar to be the next U.S. solicitor general at the Department of Justice, the White House announced Wednesday morning.

value.title: Trump was 'in pain and afraid' from COVID-19, says niece Mary Trump
value.excerpt: The former president’s niece made the claim in a new book. Former President Trump was allegedly “in pain and afraid” after he contracted the coronavirus back in early October. Mary claimed that he was struggling to breathe while playing up theatrical his return.

value.title: Biden nominates Elizabeth Prelogar to be solicitor general
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Wednesday nominated acting US Solicitor General Elizabeth Prelogar to permanently take on the role of representing the US government in cases before the Supreme Court.

value.title: Federal prosecutors came to suspect Trump Org CFO Allen Weisselberg lied
value.excerpt: New York federal prosecutors came to suspect the Trump Organization's chief financial officer, Allen Weisselberg, lied in testimony during their investigation of former Trump personal attorney Michael Cohen three years ago, according to four people familiar with prosecutors' thinking.

value.title: LA Times' 'Covering Kamala Harris' Instagram account inactive since May, dials back coverage
value.excerpt: The Los Angeles Times has significantly dialed back its coverage of Vice President Harris after the California paper laid out the red carpet for the first female VP when she was sworn into office.

value.title: Atlanta US attorney who quit amid Trump's attacks to speak to Senate Judiciary Committee
value.excerpt: The Senate Judiciary Committee on Wednesday will interview Byung "BJay" Pak, the former US attorney in Atlanta who departed abruptly from the role amid then-President Donald Trump's attacks on Georgia's election results.

value.title: MSNBC opinion piece argues 'Why Ron DeSantis is more dangerous than Trump' ahead of 2024
value.excerpt: Conservative pundits have long predicted ahead of 2024 that members of the media would insist that Republican Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis would be a “worse” president than President Trump. Well, one MSNBC opinion piece is way ahead of schedule.

value.title: Biden 'checking' if he has power to intervene against Florida and Texas mask mandate bans
value.excerpt: Biden said he is “checking” on if his presidential powers could give him the ability to intervene in states banning mask mandates

value.title: Biden on Cuomo's resignation: 'I respect the governor's decision'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden said Tuesday that he respects New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo's decision to resign after the President called on Cuomo to step down last week following an official report that said Cuomo sexually harassed multiple women.

value.title: Biden White House recruits TikTok influencer Benny Drama for eyebrow-raising vaccine video
value.excerpt: The White House recruited social media comedian Benny Drama for another digital push to convince the COVID-19 vaccine-hesitant population to get the jab.

value.title: Time's Up co-founder Robbie Kaplan sued Donald Trump and Nazis. But she's also helped at least 3 targets of sex misconduct claims.
value.excerpt: Robbie Kaplan is well-known for her progressive legal work. But her work for clients accused of sexual misconduct cover-ups has reared its head.

value.title: China hawk Mike Gallagher bridges GOP’s establishment, Trump wings
value.excerpt: Mike Gallagher never intended to be in Washington for the long haul. Since being elected in 2016, the Wisconsin Republican has advocated for congressional reforms such as term limits and lobbying restrictions for officeholders.

value.excerpt: President Joe Biden called the $1 trillion infrastructure bill “historic” and said that it will “transform America.” The bill will make a huge investment in nation’s roads, public transit, water and broadband.

value.title: Joe Biden’s own Delaware homies hit back hard at vaccine mandates

value.title: VP Harris' husband to represent US at Paralympic Games in Tokyo
